    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0233"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mlle. Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-01-28">Jan 28th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-01-28">Jan 28th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            Its very
            difficult to write you
            a letter from here, because
            of the hurry and lack 
            of privacy, and its too
            bad for there are several
            things of interest.
            </p><p>
            I received your
            sweet letter of the 24th
            &mdash; faster mail than at the
            front isn’t it? &mdash; and
            am glad to know you 
            have had a little rest.
            Paul wrote me &mdash; I should
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0235" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            have seen you after the 
            Ballet &mdash; Oh well &mdash; lots
            of time.
            </p><p>
            I am still running
            in luck here and
            passing along.  I shall
            start on my voyages
            in a week if my luck
            and the weather and
            machines hold out.  I
            have finished up the
            stunts required for a 
            civilian brevet &mdash; finished
            to day, and now for 
            the harder military
            tasks.  I may be breveted
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0234" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            within two days.  I
            do not know whether
            I shall take my six
            day permission then
            and go to Paris, or 
            wait and see what
            they’re going to do
            with me.  I’ve decided
            not to get a new
            uniform until the
            khaki one gives out.
            No use, as I wear
            bathers nearly all
            the time, and the
            khaki still looks well
            enough.  No chance here
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0236" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            to order one anyway.
            </p><p>
            What I’m trying to
            figure out is how
            anyone shoots out of
            an aero.  To run it is
            hard enough.  Heavens
            if I try to move a 
            hand  to pull down 
            my casque or something
            the blooming thing begins
            to flop and dip and
            heave and run away.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Good night.
            Best to M. and Madame Guerin.</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim.</signed>
        		</closer>	
            
